ionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530416\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ntc1665702921573.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ntc1665702921573.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ntc1665702921573.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ntc1665702921573\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Frames-Within-Frames Design\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Components give access to the user view of a business activity. A crucial part of the design of a Uniface component is the frames-within-frames diagram. Access path analysis requires a frames-within-frames definition for the Uniface component under consideration.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ntc1665702921573__p_d45716e1_d45717e1_d45718e1\">A frames-within-frames diagram shows the entities that are accessed as entity frames painted inside other entity frames. The sequence in which the frames are nested defines the order in which the component accesses the entities, starting with the outermost entity. The definition reflects the access profile of the component. It helps in answering the following questions:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ntc1665702921573__li_d22877e1_d22878e1_d22879e1\">Does the component implement the required user view?\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ntc1665702921573__li_d22880e1_d22881e1_d22882e1\">Is the component susceptible to performance bottle-necks?\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ntc1665702921573__p_d45719e1_d45720e1_d45721e1\">The following illustrations show an example of the frames-within-frames diagram and the access profile it is based on.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"ntc1665702921573__fig_d45722e1_d45723e1_d45724e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Frames-Within-Frames Diagram</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Frames-within-frames diagram\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/frameswithinframes.jpg?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"ntc1665702921573__fig_d45728e1_d45729e1_d45730e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 2. </span>Access Profile</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Access profile\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/accessprofile.jpg?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530416\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530416\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Frames-Within-Frames Design Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Frames-Within-Frames Design Components give access to the user view of a business activity. A crucial part of the design of a Uniface component is the frames-within-frames diagram. Access path analysis requires a frames-within-frames definition for the Uniface component under consideration. A frames-within-frames diagram shows the entities that are accessed as entity frames painted inside other entity frames. The sequence in which the frames are nested defines the order in which the component accesses the entities, starting with the outermost entity. The definition reflects the access profile of the component. It helps in answering the following questions: Does the component implement the required user view? Is the component susceptible to performance bottle-necks? The following illustrations show an example of the frames-within-frames diagram and the access profile it is based on. Figure 1. Frames-Within-Frames Diagram Figure 2. Access Profile Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}